SOURCE      mitochondrion Fusarium odoratissimum (Fusarium oxysporum f. sp.
            cubense tropical race 4)
  ORGANISM  Fusarium odoratissimum
            Eukaryota; Fungi; Dikarya; Ascomycota; Pezizomycotina;
            Sordariomycetes; Hypocreomycetidae; Hypocreales; Nectriaceae;
            Fusarium; Fusarium oxysporum species complex.
REFERENCE   1
  AUTHORS   Brankovics,B., Zhang,H., van Diepeningen,A.D., van der Lee,T.A.,
            Waalwijk,C. and de Hoog,G.S.
  TITLE     GRAbB: Selective Assembly of Genomic Regions, a New Niche for
            Genomic Research
  JOURNAL   PLoS Comput. Biol. 12 (6), E1004753 (2016)
   PUBMED   27308864
  REMARK    Publication Status: Online-Only
REFERENCE   2  (bases 1 to 49697)
  AUTHORS   Brankovics,B.
  TITLE     Direct Submission
  JOURNAL   Submitted (22-APR-2016) BYP, CBS, 8 Uppsalalaan, 3584 CT Utrecht,
            3511KT, Utrecht, NETHERLANDS
COMMENT     The selective assembly was performed using GRAbB
            (https://github.com/b-brankovics/grabb. The following software
            versions were used: MIRA 4.0, seqtk 1.1-r91 and SPAdes 3.7.1 GRAbB
            was run on the SRR550152 read files using NC_017930 (INSDC
            accession number) FASTA file as reference and using a modified
            version of external_skeleton.pl (from the GRAbB package). The
            overlapping ends of the three assembled contigs were identified and
            trimmed manually to form a single circular sequence.
